Infinite After Verbs

We can use the infinite (to + verb) of certain verbs after other common verbs.

I want to go. 
He agreed to do it.
She promised to meet him.
They offered to help.

To form the negative, add not after to.

I agreed to not say something.

Common verbs that can be followed by the infinite include: 
agree
ask
begin
decide
hope
like
love
offer
prefer
promise
refuse
seem 
start
try
want 
wish
